---
---

<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-bg"></div>
  <div class="container hero-content">
    <h1>
      An <span class="accent">Abject-Oriented</span> OS
    </h1>
    <p class="hero-hook">
      Describe what you want. An <em>abject</em> appears, window and all,
      and it keeps working after you stop talking to it.
    </p>
    <p class="hero-sub">
      For anyone, not just developers. Free, open source, and local-first:
      your machine, your data, no cloud, no code required.
    </p>
    <div class="hero-actions">
      <a href="#downloads" class="btn btn-primary">Download</a>
      <a href="#summon" class="btn btn-outline">Build from Source</a>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-demo">
      <video autoplay loop muted playsinline>
        <source src="/abject_demo2_1080.webm" type="video/webm" />
      </video>
      <p class="hero-demo-caption">
        Live capture, not a mockup: a task list spoken into existence.
        The window opens because it was asked to.
      </p>
    </div>
    <p class="hero-desc">
      An <em>abject</em> is not an app. It is a small living object (a window, an agent,
      a tool, a peer) that carries its own description, talks to its neighbors through
      messages, and answers for itself in plain English.
      Ask any abject what it is, and it will tell you. Politely.
      <a href="/ask-protocol" class="thesis-link">Read the Ask Protocol &rarr;</a>
    </p>
    <div class="hero-glyphs">
      <div class="hero-glyph">
        <span class="glyph-icon">{'{'}?{'}'}</span>
        <span class="glyph-text">Objects that explain themselves</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-glyph">
        <span class="glyph-icon">{'{'}!{'}'}</span>
        <span class="glyph-text">Objects that repair their own plumbing</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-glyph">
        <span class="glyph-icon">{'{'}*{'}'}</span>
        <span class="glyph-text">Software that grows by adoption</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="hero-tagline">
      abject <span class="dim">(n.)</span> 1. an AI object. 2. &lsquo;utterly hopeless&rsquo;.
      Anyone who has maintained object-oriented code knows the two meanings are compatible.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .hero {
    position: relative;
    min-height: 100vh;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    padding-top: 64px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .hero-bg {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background:
      radial-gradient(ellipse 60% 50% at 50% 30%, rgba(91, 229, 160, 0.07) 0%, transparent 60%),
      radial-gradient(ellipse 40% 40% at 70% 20%, rgba(139, 123, 255, 0.05) 0%, transparent 50%),
      radial-gradient(ellipse 30% 30% at 30% 60%, rgba(91, 229, 160, 0.04) 0%, transparent 50%);
    pointer-events: none;
    animation: pulse-glow 8s ease-in-out infinite;
  }

  .hero-content {
    position: relative;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }

  .hero-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--eldritch);
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    animation: pulse-glow 4s ease-in-out infinite;
  }

  h1 {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    text-shadow: 0 0 40px rgba(91, 229, 160, 0.1);
    animation: glitch 12s infinite;
  }

  .accent {
    color: var(--eldritch);
    text-shadow: 0 0 30px var(--eldritch-glow-strong);
  }

  .hero-hook {
    max-width: 640px;
    margin: 0 auto 1rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .hero-hook em {
    color: var(--eldritch);
  }

  .hero-sub {
    max-width: 620px;
    margin: 0 auto 2rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .hero-desc {
    max-width: 620px;
    margin: 3rem auto 2rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .hero-tagline {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    max-width: 560px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .hero-tagline .dim {
    opacity: 0.6;
  }

  .hero-actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .hero-glyphs {
    display: flex;
    gap: 2rem;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .hero-glyph {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.6rem;
  }

  .glyph-icon {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--eldritch);
    background: var(--eldritch-glow);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-accent);
    padding: 0.25rem 0.45rem;
    border-radius: 5px;
    animation: breathe 4s ease-in-out infinite;
  }

  .hero-glyph:nth-child(2) .glyph-icon {
    color: var(--void-purple);
    background: var(--void-purple-glow);
    border-color: rgba(139, 123, 255, 0.2);
    animation-delay: 1.3s;
  }

  .hero-glyph:nth-child(3) .glyph-icon {
    animation-delay: 2.6s;
  }

  .glyph-text {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }

  @keyframes breathe {
    0%, 100% { box-shadow: 0 0 6px rgba(91, 229, 160, 0.1); }
    50% { box-shadow: 0 0 14px rgba(91, 229, 160, 0.25); }
  }

  .thesis-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
    color: var(--eldritch-dim);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(43, 204, 110, 0.3);
    padding-bottom: 1px;
    transition: color 0.2s, border-color 0.2s;
  }

  .thesis-link:hover {
    color: var(--eldritch);
    border-bottom-color: var(--eldritch);
  }

  .hero-demo {
    margin-top: 0;
    max-width: 900px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  .hero-demo video {
    width: 100%;
    border-radius: 12px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    box-shadow: 0 0 40px rgba(91, 229, 160, 0.08);
  }

  .hero-demo-caption {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    font-style: italic;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .hero-actions {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
    }
    .hero-glyphs {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 1rem;
    }
  }
</style>
